   <body>
      <context>
         <hazardstatement type="danger">
            <messagepanel>
               <typeofhazard>hazard of electric shock, explosion, or arc flash</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid>
                  <sl>
                     <sli>Electrical equipment must be installed, operated, serviced, and
maintained only by qualified personnel.</sli>
                     <sli>Apply appropriate personal protective equipment (PPE) and follow
safe electrical work practices.</sli>
                     <sli>Disconnection devices for AC and DC must be provided by others,
be readily accessible, and the function of the disconnection device
marked for its function.</sli>
                     <sli>Turn off all power supplying the UPS system before working on
or inside the equipment.</sli>
                     <sli>Before working on the UPS system, check for hazardous voltage
between all terminals including the protective earth.</sli>
                     <sli>The UPS contains an internal energy source. Hazardous voltage
can be present even when disconnected from the mains supply. Before
installing or servicing the UPS system, ensure that the units are
OFF and that mains and batteries are disconnected. Wait five minutes
before opening the UPS to allow the capacitors to discharge.</sli>
                     <sli>The UPS must be properly earthed/grounded and due to a high leakage
current, the earthing/grounding conductor must be connected first.</sli>
                  </sl>
               </howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <note>This procedure is only applicable
to 75â€“100 kVA systems.</note>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the four indicated covers in the given order.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/replace_0j-0n10758_75-100kw_sscboxass_remove4covers_w120mm_0000193381.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the four screws and loosen the two nuts, and tilt
the SBS connection box outwards.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/replace_0j-0n10758_75-100kw_sscboxass_tiltpcba_w120mm_0000193420.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the four screws from the fan module.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Slide out the fan module far enough to disconnect the cables.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Note the location of the cables connected to the fan module
and disconnect the cables.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the fan module.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/replace_0j-0n10758_75-100kw_sscboxass_removefanass_w120mm_0000204967.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Note the location of the cables from the static switch
controller box that are connected to the contactor and disconnect
the cables.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/replace_0j-0n10758_75-100kw_sscboxass_disconnectcablescontactor_w120mm_0000193419.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the two screws and slide out the static switch controller
box.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/replace_0j-0n10758_75-100kw_sscboxass_slideoutssc_w120mm_0000193418.png"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the static switch controller box.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/replace_0j-0n-10758_75-100kw_sscboxass__changessc_w120mm_0000193417.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Reverse the procedure for installation of the replacement
static switch controller box.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
